A rectangular piece of glass and a triangular piece of glass are joined to make a window. The area of the triangular piece of glass is $30$ square feet. Find the total area of the window.

\begin{tikzpicture}
% Triangle on top
\draw (0,0) -- (2,0) -- (1,2) -- cycle;
\node[above] at (1,2) {6 ft};
% Rectangle below
\draw (0,0) -- (2,0) -- (2,-2.5) -- (0,-2.5) -- cycle;
\node[below] at (1,-2.5) {9 ft};
\node[left] at (0,-1.25) {7 ft};
\end{tikzpicture}

The total area of the window is \underline{\hspace{1cm}} square feet.
